info.description:
Collection for testing FikaTutor Document to JSON Converter API

**Features:**
- Single or multiple file uploads
- Supports PDF, DOC, DOCX, PPT, PPTX
- Converts documents to structured JSON format
- No file count limit (configurable)

**JSON Format:**
{
  "subject_name": {
    "title": "",
    "description": "",
    "chapters": [
      {
        "title": "",
        "topics": [
          {
            "topic_id": "",
            "title": "",
            "content": "",
            "examples": [],
            "real_world_applications": [],
            "keywords": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}

request.description:
Upload multiple documents and convert them to JSON format.

**How to use:**
1. Add multiple entries with the same key 'file'
2. Set type to 'File' for each entry
3. Select different files for each entry
4. All files will be processed and returned in a single response

**Supported formats:** PDF, DOC, DOCX, PPT, PPTX

**Response format for multiple files:**
{
  "results": [
    {
      "filename": "document1.pdf",
      "status": "success",
      "data": {
        "subject_name": {
          "title": "",
          "description": "",
          "chapters": [...]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "filename": "document2.pdf",
      "status": "success",
      "data": { ... }
    }
  ],
  "summary": {
    "total_files": 2,
    "successful": 2,
    "failed": 0
  }
}

**Notes:**
- No file count limit by default (configurable via MAX_FILES_PER_REQUEST)
- Processing is sequential (10-30 seconds per file)
- Large documents (400+ pages) may take 1-3 minutes each
- Each file's JSON follows the exact format with subject_name, chapters, topics structure
